<item>
            <title>[LU-9921] LNet peer discovery list handling</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9921</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In lnet_destroy_peer_locked() we should add an assertion that the lp_dc_pendq list is empty. Similarly for lnet_destroy_peer_ni_locked() and lpni_peer_nis, lpni_on_remote_peer_ni_list, .... The list heads added and modified by the dynamic discovery series should be audited.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In lnet_peer_discovery_complete() the list handing appears unsafe. lnet_send() and lnet_finalize() may/will modify msg_list. So list_for_each_entry_safe() must be used. Based on how other code used msg_list, it looks like we need to call list_del() or list_del_init() before calling either function. At the end of lnet_peer_discovery_complete() we should assert that pending_msgs is empty. The dynamic discovery series should be audited for similarly unsafe list handling.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;List heads in the_lnet should be statically initialized.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
